The National Working Committee (NWC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has named three-member appeal committees for the recently conducted primaries for Kogi and Bayelsa governorship elections. A statement signed by the party’s National Publicity Secretary, Malam Lanre Issa-Onilu, said the Kogi Indirect Primary Appeal Committee has Senator Abdullahi Umar Yandoma as chairman; Hajiya Amina Muhammed, secretary; and Tony McFoy,  member. The Bayelsa Direct Primary Appeal Committee has Barrister Shuaibu Aruwa as chairman; Edith Newman Amadi, secretary; and Abdul Malik El-Yakub, member. Chief David Lyon won the APC governorship ticket in Bayelsa State, while incumbent Governor Yahaya Bello secured the ticket in Kogi State at their separate primaries. Kogi election: APC inaugurates 7 man screening committee Bayelsa: Suspense, anxiety as aspirants scramble for APC gov’ship ticket APC shifts Bayelsa gov’ship primary OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY